============================================================================
A) ABOUT ELSI
============================================================================

   ELSI provides and enhances open-source software packages which solve or
   circumvent eigenvalue problems in self-consistent field calculations
   based on the Kohn-Sham density-functional theory.

   Visit the ELSI Interchange website for more information:

     http://elsi-interchange.org

   For questions, please email:

     elsi-team@duke.edu

============================================================================
B) INSTALLATION OF ELSI
============================================================================

   The standard installation of ELSI requires:

   *  CMake 3.0 or newer
   *  A Fortran compiler supporting the Fortran 2003 standard
   *  A C compiler supporting the C99 standard
   *  A C++ compiler supporting the C++11 standard
   *  An MPI library
   *  BLAS, LAPACK, (BLACS,) and ScaLAPACK libraries
   *  PtScotch 6.0.4 or newer
      (available at https//gforge.inria.fr/projects/scotch)

   The installation process is:

   *  mkdir build
   *  cd build
   *  cmake [options] ..
   *  make
   *  make install

   Installation of ELSI with GNU, Intel, PGI, XL, and Cray compilers has
   been tested.

   Please refer to the "INSTALL" file for a complete description.

